# CinemaVerse MCU Viewing App - API Configuration
# 
# This file contains environment variable templates for optional API enrichment.
# All keys are OPTIONAL - the app works fully offline with bundled JSON and posters.
# 
# SECURITY: Never commit real API keys. Use environment variables or CI/CD secrets.
#
# Android Build Integration:
#   During Gradle configuration, the build system reads these variables from your shell:
#   export OMDB_API_KEY="YOUR_REAL_KEY"
#   export TMDB_API_KEY="YOUR_REAL_KEY"
#   export TMDB_READ_ACCESS_TOKEN="YOUR_REAL_TOKEN"
#   ./gradlew :app:assembleGithubDebug
#
# Web/Framework Compatibility:
#   Also includes VITE_, NEXT_PUBLIC_, and unprefixed aliases for multi-environment support.

# ============================================================================
# OMDb API (Open Movie Database)
# ============================================================================
# Provides ratings, plot summaries, runtime, IMDb ID, and cast information
# 
# Get your free/paid key at: https://www.omdbapi.com/apikey.aspx
# Free tier: 1,000 requests/day (sufficient for periodic enrichment)
# 
# Used for: Title ratings, extended plots, language, runtime enhancement
OMDB_API_KEY=YOUR_OMDB_API_KEY_HERE
VITE_OMDB_API_KEY=YOUR_OMDB_API_KEY_HERE
NEXT_PUBLIC_OMDB_API_KEY=YOUR_OMDB_API_KEY_HERE

# ============================================================================
# TMDB API (The Movie Database)
# ============================================================================
# Provides posters, backdrops, cast, crew, ratings, and production metadata
#
# Get your free API key at: https://www.themoviedb.org/settings/api
# Free tier: Sufficient for full MCU coverage
#
# Two types of authentication:
#
#   1. API Key (v3) - Used for read operations
#      - Less secure (visible in client requests if exposed)
#      - Suitable for optional client-side enrichment
#      - Less rate-limited than Read Access Token
TMDB_API_KEY=YOUR_TMDB_API_KEY_HERE
VITE_TMDB_API_KEY=YOUR_TMDB_API_KEY_HERE
NEXT_PUBLIC_TMDB_API_KEY=YOUR_TMDB_API_KEY_HERE

#   2. Read Access Token (v4) - Recommended for server-side use
#      - More secure (should not be exposed to clients)
#      - Use in backend proxy or API endpoint
#      - Higher rate limits
#      - Bearer token authentication (header: "Authorization: Bearer TOKEN")
TMDB_READ_ACCESS_TOKEN=YOUR_TMDB_READ_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
VITE_TMDB_READ_ACCESS_TOKEN=YOUR_TMDB_READ_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
NEXT_PUBLIC_TMDB_READ_ACCESS_TOKEN=YOUR_TMDB_READ_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

# ============================================================================
# Optional: Vercel Environment (for deployed web apps)
# ============================================================================
# If deploying the web version to Vercel, configure these in project Settings > Environment Variables
# - Set to "Production" environment only if using real keys
# - Leave blank if running locally without API enrichment

# ============================================================================
# Metadata Enrichment Priority
# ============================================================================
# When loading MCU titles, the app follows this artwork and data priority:
#
# 1. Bundled local asset poster (/android_asset/mcu_posters/xxx.jpg)
#    - Always present (offline guaranteed)
#    - No API call needed
#
# 2. Local curated override (from ViewingLists.kt)
#    - Hand-picked poster URLs or local paths
#    - Developer-configured only
#
# 3. TMDB poster (if TMDB_API_KEY or TMDB_READ_ACCESS_TOKEN provided)
#    - High-quality official artwork
#    - Dynamic based on TMDB database
#    - Network call required
#
# 4. OMDb poster (if OMDB_API_KEY provided)
#    - IMDb-sourced artwork
#    - Fallback for TMDB misses
#    - Network call required
#
# 5. Built-in fallback (MCU-themed gradient)
#    - Always works offline
#    - Used when no poster available
#
# Metadata (ratings, plots, cast, crew):
#   - Local curated metadata used first (from JSON + ViewingLists.kt)
#   - TMDB data fills gaps (requires API key)
#   - OMDb data supplements further (requires API key)

# ============================================================================
# Getting Started (No API Keys)
# ============================================================================
#
# The app is fully usable without any API keys configured:
#
#   $ ./gradlew :app:assembleGithubDebug
#   $ adb install app/build/outputs/apk/github/debug/app-github-debug.apk
#
# Features available offline:
#   ✓ All 50+ MCU titles with posters
#   ✓ Complete viewing order (release, timeline, phase, saga)
#   ✓ Phase and saga grouping
#   ✓ Search by title
#   ✓ Filter by phase/saga/type
#   ✓ About section with credits
#   ✗ TMDB/OMDb ratings and enriched metadata

# ============================================================================
# Getting Started (With API Keys)
# ============================================================================
#
# To enable metadata enrichment:
#
#   1. Get free API keys:
#      - OMDb: https://www.omdbapi.com/apikey.aspx (1,000 req/day free)
#      - TMDB: https://www.themoviedb.org/settings/api (unlimited free)
#
#   2. Export environment variables:
#      $ export OMDB_API_KEY="your-actual-key"
#      $ export TMDB_API_KEY="your-actual-key"
#      $ export TMDB_READ_ACCESS_TOKEN="your-actual-token"
#
#   3. Build and run:
#      $ ./gradlew :app:assembleGithubDebug
#      $ adb install app/build/outputs/apk/github/debug/app-github-debug.apk
#
#   4. Verify in About screen:
#      - "Metadata providers: TMDB, OMDb"
#      - Posters load from TMDB if available
#      - Ratings appear for enriched titles

# ============================================================================
# CI/CD and Deployment
# ============================================================================
#
# GitHub Actions (if configured in .github/workflows/):
#   - Add secrets via Settings > Secrets and variables > Actions
#   - Reference in workflow: ${{ secrets.OMDB_API_KEY }}
#
# Vercel (web version):
#   - Add to project Settings > Environment Variables
#   - Set to "Production" for deployed version only
#   - Local development can use .env.local (not committed)
#
# Never commit API keys directly to git.

